message.content:
1. The CR rate was significantly improved at all intervals in Group P+D compared with Group P2.5.
2. The CR rate was not significantly improved at 4–72 h in Group P+D compared with Group P2.5.
3. The CR rate was elevated at 24–72 h in Group P7.5 compared with Group P2.5.
4. The difference in CR rates between the groups was statistically significant (P<0.05).
